Noon (12:05:00) in the Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes—Aric leans closer to the mysterious blank book, holding it up toward the stained-glass windows where multicolored light filters through.

You tilt the book at different angles, watching those faint shadows dance beneath the pages. They move like smoke trapped in amber, never quite forming a recognizable shape. The leather cover is unnaturally smooth—cool to the touch despite the warm midday light flooding through the windows. As you flip through the blank pages, they make no sound. No rustle, no whisper. The pages seem to absorb sound entirely.

Then you notice something else.

In the center of the front cover, barely visible unless the light hits it just right, is a symbol embossed into the leather—a circle containing an eye, but the eye has six pupils arranged in a hexagonal pattern. It sends a chill down your spine.

The elderly librarian's voice cuts through the silence. "Ah," he says, his tone shifting from casual interest to something more guarded. "You've found the Hexaphrenicon. I wondered when someone would."

He pushes back from his desk, the chair creaking beneath him. "Acquired three months ago from a dying explorer's estate. Never could classify it." He adjusts his spectacles. "Dangerous thing, truly. But then again..." A thin smile crosses his weathered face. "The most dangerous books often contain the most valuable knowledge."

